# Next.js Frontend Standards

## Architecture

- Next.js 14 + App Router (`apps/web/src/app/`)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS v4 + `@tailwindcss/postcss`
- Backend calls via `NodeStayClient` from `@nodestay/api-client`
- Shared types from `@nodestay/domain`

## Route Structure

| Route | Page |
|-------|------|
| `/` | Home |
| `/venues` | Venue listing |
| `/venues/[venueId]` | Venue details + pricing plans |
| `/passes` | My passes |
| `/sessions` | Session / timer |
| `/compute` | Compute marketplace |
| `/merchant/compute` | Venue node management |

## Coding Conventions

- UI copy is in **Japanese**
- Default to Server Components; use `'use client'` only when interactivity is needed
- Layout components live in `src/components/layout/` (Header, Footer)
- API client is instantiated in `src/services/nodestay.ts`
- Use `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix for client-visible environment variables

## Key Environment Variables

- `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL` — Backend API URL (default `http://localhost:3001`)
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_ACCESS_PASS_NFT_ADDRESS` — AccessPassNFT contract address
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_DEPOSIT_VAULT_ADDRESS` — DepositVault contract address
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_CHAIN_ID` — Target chain ID

## Testing

- Vitest + @testing-library/react
- Coverage threshold: 80% (v8)
- Run: `npm run test -w @nodestay/web`
